                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d745">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/520a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-17T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 17, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>907. The Soviet Ambassador today asked if the American Government would be
                    willing to receive a Soviet military mission to the United States composed of
                    approximately six officers headed by Lieutenant-General Golikov.<note n="40"
                        xml:id="d745fn40">This Soviet Military Mission arrived by airplane in New
                        York on July 26, 1941. Lt. Gen. Filip Ivanovich Golikov, Deputy Chief of
                        Staff, was Chief of the Mission: Division Engineer Alexander Konstantinovich
                        Repin was Assistant Chief; and 1st Lt. Nikolay Vasilyevich Evsikov was the
                        Secretary.</note> The purpose of this mission, the Ambassador said, would be
                    to supervise the placing of Soviet orders and to cooperate with the American
                    authorities in the procurement of supplies and equipment for the Soviet
                    Union.</p>
                <p>After discussing the matter with the President and the War Department, I have
                    informed the Ambassador that this Government would be pleased to receive such a
                    mission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
